<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1606,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Knuth" authorityYear="1912" box="[151,388,1607,1632]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="integrifolia">
<emphasis box="[151,388,1607,1632]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Balbisia integrifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from all other species in 
<collectingCountry box="[955,1044,1606,1632]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1056,1110,1606,1632]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1168,1231,1606,1632]" name="Chile" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Chile</collectingCountry>
by its undivided, ovate-acuminate leaves. Its range extends into northern 
<collectingCountry box="[820,938,1645,1671]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and is likely closely related to two other, Argentinian species, also with undivided leaves: 
<taxonomicName authority="(I. M. Johnst.) Descole, O'Donell &amp; Lourteig" authorityName="Descole, O'Donell &amp; Lourteig" authorityYear="1939" baseAuthorityName="I. M. Johnst." box="[729,1385,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="miniata">
<emphasis box="[729,852,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">B. miniata</emphasis>
(I.M.Johnst.) Descole, O'Donell &amp; Lourteig
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gris.) Hunz. &amp; Ariza Espinar." box="[151,651,1722,1748]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calycina">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1723,1748]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">B. calycina</emphasis>
(Gris.) Hunz. &amp; Ariza Espinar.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
